Aim: To analyze the customer data provided after EDA.¶

Problem Statement :¶

To predict Interest Rate based on given customer data.¶

  • ID -- Unique Loan ID
  • Amount.Requested -- Amount of money requested by the borrower
  • Interest. Rate -- Interest Rate on the loan [<- Dependent variable]
  • Loan. Length -- Number of payments (36 or 60)
  • Loan. Purpose -- Reason for loan provided by borrower
  • Debt.To.Income.Ratio -- All your monthly debt payments divided by your gross monthly income
  • Home. Ownership -- Home ownership status: (RENT, OWN, MORTGAGE, OTHERS)
  • Monthly. Income -- Monthly income of borrower
  • Open. CREDIT. Lines -- The number of open credit lines
  • Revolving.CREDIT. Balance -- Type of credit Balance that can be used repeatedly up to a certain limit as long as the account is open, and payments are made on time. With revolving credit, the amount of available credit
  • Inquiries.in.the.Last.6.Months -- A credit inquiry is a request by an institution for credit report information from a credit reporting agency
  • Employment.Length – Employment period
  • FICO -- FICO credit score of the borrower (https://www.investopedia.com/terms/f/ficoscore.asp)

Checking for missing value in Numerical features and treating them¶

In [17]:
def treat_num_columns(col_list):
    
    for i in col_list:
        col_name = i
        print('Independent Variable: ',col_name)
        print('Check if there are any missing value in variable',col_name,': ')
        if (loan_data[col_name].isnull().any().any() == True):
            print('No. of Observations with missing value: ', loan_data[col_name].isnull().sum(axis=0))
            # Replacing missing values with Median
            loan_data[col_name].fillna(loan_data[col_name].median(), inplace=True)
            print('After treating the missing values')
            print(loan_data[col_name].isnull().sum(axis=0))
            print('')
        else:
            print('No missing values found in ',col_name)
            print('')

In [19]:
def treat_cat_columns(cat_col_list):
    
    for i in cat_col_list:
        col_name = i
        print('Independent Variable: ',col_name)
        print('Check if there are any missing value in variable',col_name,': ')
        if (loan_data[col_name].isnull().any().any() == True):
            print('No. of Observations with missing value: ', loan_data[col_name].isnull().sum(axis=0))
            # Replacing missing values with Mode
            loan_data[col_name].fillna(loan_data[col_name].mode()[0], inplace=True)
            print('After treating the missing values')
            print('No. of Observations with missing value: ', loan_data[col_name].isnull().sum(axis=0))
            print('')
        else:
            print('No missing values found in ',col_name)
            print('')
